usage: git sync [<options>]

Synchronize changes and update submodules

    -h|--help               display help
    -e|--stop-on-error      stop looping as soon as command fails (exit code != 0)
    -j<n>                   number of submodules synchronized in parallel (default to 32)
    -a|--all                visit all submodules (ignore SKU filter)
    .                       visit startup module only (do not visit submodules)

    -c|--clean              clean local branches (delete redondant ones)
    -n|--no-push            do not push local modifications
    
example:
    git sync                # synchronize working dir and submodules recursively
    git sync .              # synchronize working dir only
    git sync -n             # do not push